title: Wrong data set result returned when setting an invalid filter expression row[0]
description: When setting the filter to 'row[0] equals to 0', the data set returns the wrong result or null result set.
OB: When setting an invalid filter expression like 'row[0] equals to 0', the data set returns the wrong result or null result set.
EB: The data set should return the correct result when a valid filter expression is set. It should not return the wrong result or null result set.
SR:
To reproduce:
1. Set a filter in the data set with the expression 'row[0] equals to 0'.
2. Click on the Preview tab.

Actual result: The first result record is returned when previewing the data set.

Expected result: The data set should not consider 'row[0]' as a valid filter expression since it can only be generated after all the data is fetched. Therefore, it should return the correct result and not the first result record.
